solution: ```class Solution {
    public String baseNeg2(int n) {
        if (n == 0) return "0";
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        while (n != 0) {
            int rem = n % (-2);
            n /= -2;
            if (rem < 0) {
                rem += 2;
                n += 1;
            }
            sb.append(rem);
        }
        return sb.reverse().toString();
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(log n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Repeatedly divide by -2, adjusting remainder to 0/1 and correcting the quotient when remainder is negative. The loop runs once per digit (logarithmic in n), and the StringBuilder stores these digits.

